OL,3,C'I miss the mum that was' - the
OL,4,Creality of caring for a loved one with
OL,5,Cdementia
OL,7,F"I don't think we ever got used to the
OL,8,Ffact that that wasn't her. You have to
OL,9,Fkeep thinking, 'it isn't her'. But it
OL,10,Fis, and it hurts," she added.
OL,12,FAnnie's mother was a nurse in the NHS
OL,13,Ffor 50 years and Annie remembers her
OL,14,Fsaying she never wanted to be put into
OL,15,Fa home.
OL,17,FHowever, the family felt they had no
OL,18,Fchoice.
