OL,3,C'I miss the mum that was' - the
OL,4,Creality of caring for a loved one with
OL,5,Cdementia
OL,7,F"You get very isolated, because apart
OL,8,Ffrom your very close supporters, all
OL,9,Fyour other friendship circles have to
OL,10,Fgo. Everything has to give, because
OL,11,Fyou have to focused on your loved one."
OL,13,FTrish's husband Nick now lives in a
OL,14,Fspecialist care facility.
OL,16,F"I'm pleased to say he's very settled
OL,17,Fand happy which is marvellous. It was
OL,18,Fa gut-wrenching decision but it was
OL,19,Fthe best one for both of us," she said.
