OL,3,C'I miss the mum that was' - the
OL,4,Creality of caring for a loved one with
OL,5,Cdementia
OL,7,F"It was quite difficult to manage both
OL,8,Ftheir behaviours - and we were
OL,9,Fnoticing changes but he wasn't, and if
OL,10,Fhe did, he didn't want us to know or
OL,11,Ftalk about it.
OL,13,F"My mother's journey through dementia
OL,14,Fwas quite rapid. As a person she
OL,15,Fbecame very different.
OL,17,F"In my father's Indian culture it was
OL,18,Falways seen as a mental health issue,
OL,19,Fand a lot of the community don't like
OL,20,Fto talk about dementia."
